{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:d","text":"double"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"zoomLevel"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition to affecting the visual size and detail of features on the map,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the zoom level affects the size of the vector tiles that are loaded. At zoom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level 0, each tile covers the entire world map; at zoom level 1, it covers ¼"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the world; at zoom level 2, "},{"type":"text","text":"1"},{"type":"text","text":"⁄"},{"type":"text","text":"16"},{"type":"text","text":" of the world, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so on."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Changing the value of this property updates the map view immediately. If you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to animate the change, use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-setZoomLevel:animated:"},{"type":"text","text":" method instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/zoomLevel"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/zoomlevel"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The zoom level of the receiver."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyP